       _d_._p_a_i_n_t_._l_a_b_e_l_s -- _d_._l_a_b_e_l_s does.  These programs should  be  integrated
       in future GRASS releases.

BBUUGGSS
       If  the  user  is  running GRASS under X Windows, and the user enters a
       text label longer than 80 characters (i.e., allows text to wrap onto  a
       second  line),  X  Windows  will stop the user's GRASS graphics monitor
       without throwing the user out of GRASS.   If  this  happens,  the  user
       should simply restart a graphics monitor, using _d_._m_o_n.

